Biomedical Databases Parsers¶

cancerGenomeInterpreterParser.py¶

graphdb_builder.databases.parsers.cancerGenomeInterpreterParser.parser(databases_directory, download=True)[source]¶

This function parses and the Cancer Genome Interpreter database and extracts data on clinically relevant variants associated to cancer, validated oncogenic alterations and cancer driver mutations, and clinically relevant drug response biomarkers.

Parameters

  • databases_directory (str) – path to directory where import (.tsv) files will be written to.

  • download (bool) – download database raw file or not.

Returns

Tuple with four components. entities is a set of tuples with clinically relevant variants, alternative names, chromosome and position, PubMed reference, effect, oncogeneicity and source of the data. relationships is a dictionary of tuples where each key corresponds to a relationship type (see cancerGenomeInterpreterConfig.yml) and values are sets of tuples with the relevant data for the relationship. entities_header is a list of column names for entities tab-delimited file, while relationships_headers is dictionary of relationship files to be created and corresponding column names.

graphdb_builder.databases.parsers.disgenetParser.readDisGeNetProteinMapping(config, databases_directory)[source]¶

Parses and collects all genes and proteins present in the DisGeNET protein mapping file, and returns the data as a dictionary.

Parameters

  • config (str) –

  • databases_directory (str) – path to directory where import (.tsv) files will be written to.

Returns

Dictionary of sets with NCBI Entrez Gene Identifiers as keys and UniprotKB Identifiers as values.
